WEBVTT

00:01.043 --> 00:02.586
(TATTOOING NEEDLE BUZZING)

00:25.943 --> 00:27.236
That's it.

00:28.946 --> 00:32.241
Can I just, you know,
look at it for a minute?

00:33.450 --> 00:35.285
You're an artist, Sid.

00:37.204 --> 00:39.248
You're telling me
you're just gonna walk out of here

00:39.331 --> 00:40.958
and I'm never gonna see it again?

00:41.500 --> 00:43.293
There's a good chance of that, yes.

00:44.461 --> 00:47.965
Most guys, you know, for the first one,
they start with something small.

00:48.048 --> 00:50.968
"Mom", girlfriend's initials,
something like that.

00:51.051 --> 00:52.386
Not you.

00:53.428 --> 00:56.890
You get a full set of sleeves,
all in a couple of months.

00:56.974 --> 00:59.935
Takes guys a few years
to get the ink you got.

01:00.310 --> 01:02.312
I don't have a few years.

01:03.814 --> 01:05.440
Wish t0 hell I did.

01:58.201 --> 01:59.411
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

01:59.494 --> 02:01.038
The vault. Open it.

02:01.121 --> 02:03.707
We can't. The branch manager's not here.

02:05.626 --> 02:08.377
- Where is he?
- It's lunchtime. He's at White Castle.

02:08.461 --> 02:09.463
White Castle?

02:09.545 --> 02:13.925
It's a fast-food restaurant.
They serve those little square burgers.

02:14.384 --> 02:15.761
I know what it is.

02:16.303 --> 02:17.971
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

02:18.055 --> 02:20.515
I'm not playing games. Open it.

02:20.599 --> 02:23.060
Sir, you have a half a million dollars cash
in your bag.

02:23.143 --> 02:25.771
Don't you think it would be better if...

02:25.854 --> 02:27.356
(POLICE SIRENS WAILING)

02:35.947 --> 02:39.743
<i>OFFICER: (ON LOUDSPEAKER) This is
the police. You are completely surrounded.</i>

02:42.162 --> 02:43.955
<i>Put down your weapon.</i>

02:45.791 --> 02:48.293
<i>Put down your weapons now!</i>

02:52.339 --> 02:56.134
Rarely in the case of armed robbery
do we hear a plea of "No Contest."

02:56.426 --> 02:59.763
- Are you sure about this, Mr. Scofield?
- I'm sure, Your Honor.

03:00.097 --> 03:01.932
Your Honor, we'd like to recess
if we could.

03:02.015 --> 03:04.101
My client's a bit confused at the moment.

03:04.184 --> 03:06.269
- I'm not, Your Honor.
- He is, Your Honor.

03:06.353 --> 03:09.147
Perhaps you should heed
your representation's advice.

03:09.231 --> 03:11.733
Take some additional time
to consider your response.

03:11.817 --> 03:14.277
I've already done that, Your Honor.

03:19.616 --> 03:22.244
I'll retire to my chambers
to determine sentencing.

03:22.327 --> 03:24.413
Court's recessed until 1:30.

03:26.289 --> 03:27.624
Okay, come on, let's go.

03:27.708 --> 03:28.959
Uncle Mike.

03:30.919 --> 03:32.379
I didn't want you to come.

03:32.796 --> 03:34.256
Go home, LJ.

03:34.798 --> 03:36.508
I didn't want you to see this.

03:44.182 --> 03:47.352
- He's not going to take this well.
- Can you blame him? He's your nephew.

03:47.436 --> 03:48.645
He's beginning to get the idea

03:48.729 --> 03:51.940
that anybody he attaches himself to
is going to end up in prison.

03:52.023 --> 03:56.194
And he's not the only one
who is starting to feel that way, Michael.

03:56.403 --> 03:59.114
- Will you give us a minute?
- One minute.

03:59.448 --> 04:01.283
Don't you understand?

04:01.366 --> 04:03.034
You just put the book
in that woman's hand

04:03.118 --> 04:05.120
and she's going to lob it at you
like a grenade.

04:05.203 --> 04:07.581
Justice and punishment
are the same thing to her.

04:07.664 --> 04:08.707
I know.

04:08.874 --> 04:11.418
Then will you please tell me
what's going through your head?

04:11.501 --> 04:14.045
- We've been over this.
- I've known you my entire life.

04:14.129 --> 04:16.380
You don't have a violent bone
in your body.

04:16.464 --> 04:19.176
- And I know you didn't need the money.
- Veronica.

04:19.259 --> 04:21.178
Why won't you let me help you?

04:21.261 --> 04:24.347
You've been good to me my whole life.
You have.

04:25.307 --> 04:27.934
But you got to let me deal with this, okay?

04:29.060 --> 04:33.774
Given your lack of prior criminal conduct,
I am inclined toward probation.

04:33.899 --> 04:36.735
However, the fact
that you discharged a deadly weapon

04:36.818 --> 04:39.696
during the commission of the crime
suggests malice to me.

04:39.780 --> 04:42.032
For that reason, I find it incumbent

04:42.115 --> 04:45.160
that you see the inside of a prison cell,
Mr. Scofield.

04:45.869 --> 04:48.538
It says here that you've requested
to be incarcerated

04:48.622 --> 04:50.665
somewhere near your home
here in Chicago.

04:50.749 --> 04:52.209
I'm willing to honor that.

04:52.292 --> 04:54.711
- The closest Level 1 facility to...
- Level1?

04:54.795 --> 04:56.838
That's maximum security, Your Honor.

04:56.922 --> 04:59.966
I would ask counsel
to refrain from interrupting me.

05:00.050 --> 05:02.719
As I was saying, the closest Level 1 facility

05:02.803 --> 05:04.763
would be Fox River State Penitentiary.

05:04.846 --> 05:08.058
As for the term of your sentence,
I'm setting it at five years.

05:08.141 --> 05:10.644
You'll be eligible for parole
in half that time.

05:10.727 --> 05:12.938
Sentence to be carried out immediately.

05:25.408 --> 05:28.078
OFFICER 1: You people will step inside
the door. Check yourself for bugs.

05:28.161 --> 05:30.705
When you hear the knock, step out.
Keep the line moving.

05:30.789 --> 05:33.166
We ain't got all day to get this done.

05:33.416 --> 05:34.501
No talking in line.

05:34.584 --> 05:36.044
OFFICER 2: Go. Move it.
We've got less than five minutes.

05:36.127 --> 05:37.587
- Keep that line moving.
- Move it.

05:37.671 --> 05:39.506
- Keep it moving.
- Move it right now. Let's go.

05:39.589 --> 05:40.924
Move, move.

05:42.008 --> 05:44.010
Next guy in the bank.
Left. Let's go.

05:44.094 --> 05:47.973
- Name and back number.
- Scofield, Michael. 94941.

05:48.056 --> 05:50.600
- You a religious man, Scofield?
- Never really thought about it.

05:50.684 --> 05:53.019
Good, 'cause the Ten Commandments
don't mean a box of piss in here.

05:53.103 --> 05:54.563
We got two commandments and two only.

05:54.646 --> 05:56.982
The first commandment is
you got nothing coming.

05:57.065 --> 05:59.818
- What's the second commandment?
- See commandment Number 1.

06:00.610 --> 06:01.778
Got you.

06:02.362 --> 06:04.447
You talking out the side of your neck?

06:04.531 --> 06:08.034
- Come again?
- I said, are you being a smart ass?

06:08.493 --> 06:10.954
I'm just trying to fly low,
avoid the radar, boss.

06:11.037 --> 06:13.081
Do my time and get out.

06:14.291 --> 06:16.418
There isn't any flying under my radar.

06:17.002 --> 06:18.461
Good to know.

06:39.190 --> 06:41.693
Hey, can a brother get some
air-conditioning up here, cuz?

06:41.776 --> 06:43.653
It's hotter than a crack ho's mouth, man.

06:43.737 --> 06:47.032
Shit, to hell with the a.c., man.
Give me the crack ho.

06:54.122 --> 06:56.166
Yo, Fish, what you looking at?

06:56.666 --> 06:58.960
You look kind of pretty
to be up in here, man.

06:59.753 --> 07:00.921
Fish!

07:02.464 --> 07:04.799
Suggest you take a seat, Fish.

07:05.550 --> 07:08.094
Ain't nothing to do up in here
but serve time.

07:08.178 --> 07:10.013
Ain't nobody gonna serve it for you.

07:11.431 --> 07:12.682
(GROANING)

07:25.737 --> 07:27.572
Welcome to Prisneyland, Fish.

07:33.161 --> 07:35.205
(MAN CHATTERING OVER P.A.)

07:36.581 --> 07:38.124
(ALARM BUZZING)

07:54.140 --> 07:57.894
- You want to talk about it?
- It's not worth talking about.

07:57.978 --> 08:01.398
- If it's keeping you up, it is.
- It's just...

08:02.065 --> 08:03.692
It's nothing, you know.

08:04.901 --> 08:06.152
Michael's case.

08:07.237 --> 08:10.031
- You did the best you could.
- Yeah, but he didn't.

08:11.616 --> 08:14.202
He just sort of rolled over.
He didn't put up a fight.

08:14.285 --> 08:16.204
It is not like him. I...

08:17.622 --> 08:19.582
I'm sorry. I shouldn't be talking about him.

08:19.666 --> 08:22.627
Hey, if it's on your mind,
it's on your mind, right?

08:24.587 --> 08:25.755
Good night.

08:35.306 --> 08:37.392
MAN: <i>(ON</i> P.A. <i>SYSTEM) All lanes
start coming out.</i>

08:44.024 --> 08:45.942
Trey Street Deuces got the hoops.

08:46.026 --> 08:48.111
<i>Nortefios got the bleachers.</i>

08:48.445 --> 08:50.280
Woods got the weight pile.

08:50.947 --> 08:52.741
CO's got the rest.

08:53.158 --> 08:56.619
I'm telling you, the guards
are the dirtiest gang in this whole place.

08:56.703 --> 09:00.081
The only difference
between us and them is the badge.

09:00.165 --> 09:03.209
- Who's the pet lover?
- He'll deny it, but he's D.B. Cooper.

09:03.293 --> 09:06.921
Parachuted out of a plane 30 years ago,
with $1.5 million in cash.

09:07.338 --> 09:09.716
- Doesn't look like the type.
- Who does?

09:10.091 --> 09:11.843
Hey, what up, Wholesale?

09:11.926 --> 09:13.970
- You okay?
- Gonna be greater later.

09:14.054 --> 09:15.055
Yeah.

09:15.138 --> 09:18.433
- What you doing with this fish, man?
- This my new cellie.

09:18.516 --> 09:21.352
Wholesale's got it wired up
at the commissary.

09:21.436 --> 09:23.271
Anything you want, he can get it for you.

09:23.354 --> 09:25.774
You keep handing out my jacket,
I swear I'm gonna bust your grape.

09:25.857 --> 09:28.318
Man, you couldn't bust a grape in Napa
with a set of cleats on.

09:28.401 --> 09:30.612
- What are you talking about?
- Now, you want to bump your gums...

09:30.695 --> 09:32.906
Oh, no, no.
Now you're talking, talking, talking...

09:59.557 --> 10:01.017
I'm looking for someone.

10:02.936 --> 10:05.772
- A guy named Lincoln Burrows.
- Linc the Sink?

10:06.189 --> 10:08.441
- Is that what they're calling him now?
- Yeah.

10:08.525 --> 10:12.237
As in, he'll come at you with everything
but the kitchen, snowflake.

10:12.529 --> 10:13.780
Where can I find him?

10:15.532 --> 10:19.035
Man killed the Vice President's brother.
In a month, he's getting the chair.

10:19.119 --> 10:21.788
Which means no one up this river
is more dangerous than him

10:21.871 --> 10:23.289
'cause he's got nothing to lose now.

10:23.373 --> 10:25.208
What are they gonna do, kill him twice?

10:25.291 --> 10:27.043
- Is there a way I can get to him?
- Oh, no.

10:27.127 --> 10:30.338
The only time those boys get out
is for chapel and Pl.

10:30.421 --> 10:33.133
- Pl? What's that?
- Prison Industry.

10:33.258 --> 10:35.051
The guys that get along get to work.

10:35.135 --> 10:38.596
You know, painting, scrapping,
making mattresses, you name it.

10:39.639 --> 10:41.724
I wouldn't get excited though
if I were you, Fish.

10:41.808 --> 10:43.393
You ain't sniffing none of Pl.

10:43.476 --> 10:46.187
- Why is that?
-'Cause John Abruzzi runs it.

10:47.230 --> 10:50.733
-"John Abruzzi" John Abruzzi?
-"John Abruzzi" John Abruzzi.

10:51.109 --> 10:53.653
Why you want to see Burrows
so bad anyhow?

10:57.115 --> 10:59.075
Because he's my brother.

11:21.764 --> 11:23.516
LINCOLN: <i>They denied the motion.
SCOFIELD: Then do it again.</i>

11:23.600 --> 11:26.769
I can't. That's it. May 11.
That's the date, man.

11:27.103 --> 11:30.190
That's the date they,
you know, execute me.

11:30.773 --> 11:32.025
I know.

11:37.655 --> 11:41.284
- I didn't kill that man, Michael.
- The evidence says you did.

11:41.367 --> 11:44.621
I don't care what the evidence says,
I didn't kill him.

11:44.704 --> 11:45.955
Swear to me.

11:48.166 --> 11:49.834
I swear to you, Michael.

11:56.090 --> 11:59.427
But how did they get it wrong then?
The courts, the appeals?

11:59.510 --> 12:01.262
Don't know. Don't know.

12:02.138 --> 12:06.017
All I keep thinking, looking back on it,
is that I was set up.

12:06.434 --> 12:10.939
And whoever it was that set me up wants
me in the ground as quickly as possible.

12:15.318 --> 12:18.279
- What's another word for "love"?
- What's the context?

12:18.363 --> 12:19.614
Oh, you know,

12:19.697 --> 12:21.824
the "I love you so much
I ain't never knocking over

12:21.908 --> 12:23.868
"a liquor store again" context.

12:23.952 --> 12:25.662
Except, you know, classy.

12:27.497 --> 12:29.415
I'm proposing to my girl
if you got to know.

12:29.499 --> 12:30.541
In a letter?

12:30.625 --> 12:33.336
- You got a better way?
- Face to face works pretty good.

12:33.419 --> 12:36.339
This place ain't exactly the romantic spot.

12:36.839 --> 12:39.092
I'm gonna have her get on
the Staten Island Ferry.

12:39.175 --> 12:41.594
Then once she can see
the Empire State Building,

12:41.678 --> 12:44.639
she opens the letter.
It's like almost being there.

12:45.306 --> 12:48.017
Except for the fact that I won't be there.

12:48.101 --> 12:51.521
- Try "passion."
- Passion, passion. That's dope.

12:51.771 --> 12:52.939
(WHISPERING) Passion.

12:54.774 --> 12:57.360
How do you spell that? Is it P-A-S-H?

12:59.279 --> 13:00.363
No "H"?

13:06.953 --> 13:09.247
- LJ, hold up.
- Hold up?

13:10.039 --> 13:12.208
I don't know if I can go through with this.

13:12.292 --> 13:14.460
Everything's gonna be fine.

13:14.544 --> 13:15.795
Trust me.

13:26.055 --> 13:27.724
- We understand each other then?
- Yeah.

13:27.807 --> 13:31.686
- Friday. Not Saturday, not Sunday. Friday.
- It's totally understood.

13:31.769 --> 13:34.230
I don't want $100s, I don't want $5s,
I don't want $1 s.

13:34.314 --> 13:36.357
I know, I know. $10s and $20s only.

13:46.743 --> 13:47.994
It's on.

13:55.918 --> 13:57.211
(POLICE SIREN WAILING)

14:00.298 --> 14:01.466
Police!

14:24.655 --> 14:27.450
Abruzzi, I need you to hire me at Pl.

14:29.243 --> 14:30.286
Beat it.

14:31.162 --> 14:33.122
Maybe you ought to hear
what I got to say.

14:33.206 --> 14:35.124
You got nothing I need.

14:36.959 --> 14:38.753
Wouldn't be too sure of that.

14:39.754 --> 14:41.130
My mistake.

14:42.048 --> 14:43.633
Just what I need.

14:43.966 --> 14:45.301
A duck.

14:46.135 --> 14:47.637
PI, Abruzzi.

14:47.720 --> 14:50.681
You might find I can be
of more assistance than you think.

14:53.142 --> 14:54.602
Mull it over.

14:55.478 --> 14:57.855
Come find me when you're ready to talk.

15:04.821 --> 15:08.449
All right, guys, pick it up.
I want to get home tonight.

15:08.533 --> 15:09.826
Maggio.

15:16.707 --> 15:17.834
Yeah, so?

15:17.917 --> 15:20.878
That's the son of a bitch
that fingered Abruzzi.

15:20.962 --> 15:22.338
That's Fibonacci?

15:23.714 --> 15:27.760
- I thought the punk was gone forever.
- Evidently somebody found him.

15:27.844 --> 15:31.472
- Somebody messing with us?
- This you're not gonna believe.

15:35.309 --> 15:36.602
What is it?

15:41.607 --> 15:44.193
Tattoo looks fresh. Hold that.

15:45.486 --> 15:48.030
I guess being a diabetic,
you don't mind needles.

15:48.322 --> 15:50.074
I'm Michael, by the way.

15:50.158 --> 15:52.452
Scofield. I read your report.

15:52.535 --> 15:55.496
- And you are?
- Dr. Tancredi will do.

15:55.913 --> 15:57.498
Tancredi like the Governor?

15:59.542 --> 16:01.335
You're not related, are you?

16:03.838 --> 16:06.549
Wouldn't think you'd find the daughter
of "Frontier Justice" Frank

16:06.632 --> 16:08.092
working in a prison.

16:08.468 --> 16:10.219
As a doctor no less.

16:10.470 --> 16:13.556
I believe in being part of the solution,
not the problem.

16:15.349 --> 16:17.727
"Be the change
you want to see in the world."

16:21.564 --> 16:22.648
What?

16:24.275 --> 16:26.569
Nothing. That was just my senior quote.

16:26.694 --> 16:29.739
That was you? This whole time
I was thinking it was Gandhi.

16:30.740 --> 16:32.074
You're very funny.

16:32.658 --> 16:36.078
Sit tight. Put direct pressure on that.
I'll be back in a sec.

16:50.760 --> 16:54.013
So, how do we play this? You hook me up
with a few weeks' supply?

16:54.096 --> 16:56.432
Nice try. No hypos on the floor.

16:57.058 --> 16:59.769
I'm the farthest thing from a junkie.
Trust me.

16:59.936 --> 17:01.062
I got news for you, Michael.

17:01.145 --> 17:03.898
"Trust me" means absolutely zero
inside these walls.

17:03.981 --> 17:07.609
The only way you're getting that insulin
is if I'm administering it.

17:07.693 --> 17:10.404
I guess we'll be seeing
a lot of each other then.

17:10.488 --> 17:11.614
I guess so.

17:24.752 --> 17:27.128
- We're all clear on the Burrows execution.
- Good.

17:27.213 --> 17:30.800
Except for one thing.
Bishop McMorrow is not in the fold.

17:33.636 --> 17:35.972
He's got a lot of influence
with the Governor.

17:36.180 --> 17:38.391
They went to prep school
together apparently.

17:39.225 --> 17:41.102
Look, the closer it gets,

17:41.394 --> 17:44.981
the more I'm worried that the bottom
is gonna fall out of this whole thing.

17:49.193 --> 17:52.655
Maybe it's time you arranged a visit
with the good bishop then.

17:53.823 --> 17:57.034
Look, in one month it'll all be over.

17:58.202 --> 18:02.498
"The Son of man must be delivered
into the hands of sinful men,

18:02.582 --> 18:06.168
"and be crucified,
and the third day rise again."

18:06.669 --> 18:09.839
"And they remembered his words,"
and so should you.

18:10.423 --> 18:13.175
Good day, gentlemen.
May God be with you.

18:18.139 --> 18:20.349
OFFICER 1: Okay, let's go, let's go, let's go.

18:25.146 --> 18:26.355
Michael?

18:28.691 --> 18:30.192
OFFICER 2: Let's go. Come on, man.

18:32.695 --> 18:36.073
- Why?
- I'm getting you out of here.

18:36.449 --> 18:39.160
Burrows, roll it up. Happy hour's over.

18:39.702 --> 18:43.372
- It's impossible.
- Not if you designed the place, it isn't.

18:51.797 --> 18:53.049
VERONICA: Too formal.

18:55.718 --> 18:57.053
Too greeting card.

18:57.553 --> 19:00.431
Well, we got to make a decision
sooner or later, you know.

19:00.514 --> 19:03.976
- We have time.
- We don't, actually.

19:04.852 --> 19:08.105
I mean, at some point,
we got to pull the trigger on this thing.

19:08.189 --> 19:09.857
I don't want to rush this.

19:09.940 --> 19:12.610
We're only gonna do it once.
We have to get it right.

19:17.782 --> 19:21.410
- Honey, can I ask you something?
- Of course.

19:22.578 --> 19:25.414
- Are you putting this off?
- What do you mean?

19:25.498 --> 19:28.584
- I mean, are you having second thoughts?
- No.

19:29.418 --> 19:31.796
Honey, no. I'm not.

19:32.755 --> 19:35.591
I don't know, but I just
can't help thinking this is about...

19:35.675 --> 19:36.801
It's not.

19:38.260 --> 19:39.470
I love you,

19:40.346 --> 19:42.139
and I want to be your wife.

19:46.435 --> 19:49.814
-"Passion"? What were you thinking?
- Hey, you went for it.

19:49.897 --> 19:53.234
She probably thinks
I went sissy up in here. "Passion."

19:53.317 --> 19:56.362
You know, got more than one syllable,
too much talking.

19:56.445 --> 19:58.656
That's me from now on.
"One Syllable Sucre".

19:58.739 --> 19:59.949
Yes. No.

20:00.116 --> 20:01.534
Love. Hate.

20:01.909 --> 20:03.619
- Love.
- Give it time.

20:03.703 --> 20:06.539
Are you kidding? I proposed to her.

20:06.706 --> 20:10.418
That doesn't take time. Si or no.
One syllable, man.

20:13.087 --> 20:16.006
She's supposed to come around
for a conjugal on Tuesday.

20:16.090 --> 20:19.385
She's always calling me beforehand,
letting me know she's coming.

20:19.468 --> 20:22.054
This time, man, I ain't heard a peep.

20:23.222 --> 20:24.640
You spooked her.

20:25.599 --> 20:28.811
Scofield, get it together.
Pope wants to see you.

20:32.898 --> 20:34.358
No good, Fish.

20:34.817 --> 20:36.944
No one gets an audience with the Pope.

20:37.027 --> 20:40.030
Not unless he's real interested
in what you got going on.

20:41.073 --> 20:44.827
<i>POPE: Top of your class at Loyola.
Magna cum laude, in fact.</i>

20:46.328 --> 20:49.039
I can't help wondering
what someone with your credentials

20:49.123 --> 20:50.916
is doing in a place like this.

20:52.251 --> 20:54.628
Took a wrong turn
a few months back, I guess.

20:55.045 --> 20:57.173
You make it sound like a traffic infraction.

20:57.256 --> 21:00.050
Like all you did was turn the wrong way
up a one-way street.

21:00.134 --> 21:02.219
Everyone turns up one sooner or later.

21:05.681 --> 21:07.475
The reason I called you here,

21:08.517 --> 21:13.272
I noticed in your I-file, under occupation,
you put down unemployed.

21:14.231 --> 21:15.816
That's not true now, is it?

21:18.944 --> 21:21.864
I know you're
a structural engineer, Scofield.

21:25.284 --> 21:28.204
Shah Jahan built the Taj Mahal

21:28.287 --> 21:30.998
as a monument
to his undying love for his wife.

21:31.707 --> 21:33.834
My wife is quite fond of the story.

21:34.376 --> 21:36.796
It appeals to the romantic in her.

21:38.756 --> 21:42.343
Being married to someone in Corrections,
terrible job.

21:42.426 --> 21:44.512
Wouldn't wish it on anyone.

21:44.595 --> 21:49.016
And yet, in 39 years,
my wife has never complained.

21:49.600 --> 21:52.728
And the worst part of it is,
I've never thanked her.

21:54.396 --> 21:58.901
So, because I couldn't say it,
I thought, you know, I could build it.

22:00.611 --> 22:03.405
Come June, it's our 40th anniversary.

22:05.533 --> 22:07.076
But, here, look.

22:07.409 --> 22:10.412
You see, the problem is, I build any more,

22:11.080 --> 22:14.083
it's all gonna come down
like a house of cards.

22:14.166 --> 22:17.294
That's where I was hoping
you could be of assistance.

22:17.378 --> 22:21.215
And for the favor, I can offer you
three days of work a week in here,

22:21.298 --> 22:23.384
and it'll keep you off the yard.

22:30.474 --> 22:31.725
I can't do it.

22:33.811 --> 22:37.147
Son, it's better for me
to owe you one in here

22:37.231 --> 22:40.651
than it is for you to owe me one,
I can promise you that.

22:40.734 --> 22:42.528
I'll take my chances.

22:45.406 --> 22:47.408
Then we're through here.

22:47.908 --> 22:48.951
Guard!

22:51.912 --> 22:53.539
Two pounds of pot?

22:54.456 --> 22:56.709
What were you trying to do, set a record?

22:56.792 --> 22:59.795
It's not funny, LJ.
You could be going to jail.

23:01.463 --> 23:04.633
It's pretty obvious to me
you need some guidance.

23:07.928 --> 23:09.013
Thanks.

23:11.348 --> 23:12.933
From who? Old Daddy Warbucks?

23:13.017 --> 23:16.729
- Give him a chance. He's a good man.
- We got nothing in common.

23:16.812 --> 23:19.064
Oh, where's this coming from, LJ?

23:19.148 --> 23:22.359
Last semester, you were getting
almost all A's and now...

23:25.571 --> 23:28.407
- It's your father, isn't it?
- I don't have a father.

23:28.490 --> 23:31.785
It wasn't an immaculate conception,
honey, trust me.

23:34.663 --> 23:36.832
Maybe it's time we went and saw him.

23:37.917 --> 23:39.001
Mom.

23:39.209 --> 23:40.294
Ma.

23:40.628 --> 23:41.670
Don't.

23:41.754 --> 23:45.215
I'm about as excited by the prospect
as you are, but something's got to give.

23:45.299 --> 23:49.053
You have got too much potential
to be screwing up your life like this.

23:52.890 --> 23:55.976
What if they'd sent you
to Taylorville or Marion and not here?

23:56.977 --> 23:59.229
I think I'd be doing the same thing
I'm doing in here.

23:59.313 --> 24:01.523
Eating Jell-O, drinking Kool-Aid.

24:01.607 --> 24:03.400
I know what you're doing.

24:03.484 --> 24:06.987
It's not the luck of the draw
that you're in here with Lincoln.

24:07.071 --> 24:09.365
You forget I know you, both of you.

24:09.490 --> 24:13.243
You two have the most dysfunctional idea
of love I've ever seen.

24:13.327 --> 24:15.746
What, he beats you up
to keep you off the streets,

24:15.829 --> 24:18.582
so you get yourself
tossed into Fox River with him?

24:18.666 --> 24:20.834
To what? Save him?

24:23.420 --> 24:26.298
I deserve to know.
I loved him as much as you did.

24:26.382 --> 24:29.009
Past tense for you, maybe. Not me.

24:29.885 --> 24:32.721
I gave him a shot
when I got back from college. I did.

24:32.805 --> 24:34.807
Even with all the stuff
that was going on with him,

24:34.890 --> 24:37.726
I did everything I could to make it work
and he threw it away.

24:37.810 --> 24:41.689
You ever think maybe he was hurt
that you left in the first place?

24:41.772 --> 24:43.107
Don't do this.

24:43.190 --> 24:45.776
Whatever it is you're doing, don't do it.
There's a better way.

24:45.859 --> 24:47.236
I'm already appealing your case.

24:47.319 --> 24:48.445
I told you to leave that alone.

24:48.529 --> 24:50.572
I've gotten in touch with the diocese
about Lincoln.

24:50.656 --> 24:54.660
- The bishop may be able to help.
- That won't stop it. It'll only delay it.

24:58.205 --> 25:02.126
You want to do something?
You find out who's trying to bury him.

25:04.586 --> 25:06.714
Nobody's trying to bury him.

25:06.797 --> 25:09.925
- The evidence was there.
- The evidence was cooked.

25:12.720 --> 25:14.888
GUARD: Visiting hours are now over.

25:15.472 --> 25:16.974
(BELL RINGING)

25:20.144 --> 25:21.812
Take care of yourself.

25:23.647 --> 25:27.818
Someone wants him dead, Veronica.
Something more is going on here.

25:28.736 --> 25:31.405
This is desperation, Michael.
You're grabbing at straws.

25:31.488 --> 25:34.825
- You're in denial.
- Maybe. But I can't watch him die.

25:34.950 --> 25:36.326
I won't do that.

26:06.106 --> 26:07.149
Gentlemen.

26:07.232 --> 26:10.819
What is it about the Burrows situation
that I can help you with?

26:10.903 --> 26:14.823
It's our understanding that you
have great influence with the Governor.

26:14.907 --> 26:18.994
I wouldn't say it's great or influence.
We're friends.

26:19.078 --> 26:22.498
It's also our understanding
that you oppose the death penalty.

26:22.581 --> 26:24.500
I'm a man of God. How could I not?

26:24.583 --> 26:27.503
In this case, we're hoping
you'll suspend that position.

26:27.586 --> 26:29.254
At least temporarily.

26:29.546 --> 26:32.841
If the inmate appeals to me
for intervention,

26:33.342 --> 26:35.010
how can I turn my back on him?

26:35.094 --> 26:38.013
You have a habit
of answering a question with a question.

26:38.097 --> 26:41.517
And you have a way of asking questions
that beg more questions.

26:46.146 --> 26:49.983
- Are you saying you won't do it?
- I'm not a man to equivocate.

26:53.237 --> 26:56.073
You're what, 62 years old now,
Your Excellency.

26:56.156 --> 26:57.199
That's right.

26:57.282 --> 26:58.909
I would assume then
that you'd be well-versed

26:58.992 --> 27:00.828
in how our government's
tax system works.

27:00.911 --> 27:04.373
Taking personal capital gains
under the church's tax shelter...

27:04.915 --> 27:07.501
That'd be fraud, wouldn't it,
Your Excellency?

27:08.210 --> 27:11.880
I will not be cowed
into forsaking my beliefs.

27:12.422 --> 27:14.716
Not by you or anyone else.

27:15.592 --> 27:16.885
Admirable.

27:17.886 --> 27:19.513
Good day, Your Excellency.

27:20.222 --> 27:21.723
Mr. Kellerman.

27:23.183 --> 27:27.229
What is it about this case
that the Secret Service is so interested in?

27:27.312 --> 27:29.773
The man killed
the Vice President's brother.

27:37.489 --> 27:39.241
- What did you say?
- You <i>heard</i> me.

27:39.575 --> 27:42.953
Someone found Fibonacci.
I'm looking at the photos right now.

27:43.287 --> 27:47.499
<i>Son of a bitch has got a beard, sunglasses,
Witness Protection if I ever saw it.</i>

27:47.916 --> 27:49.376
Who was this someone?

27:49.459 --> 27:52.254
I don't know.
There's no return address on the envelope.

27:52.337 --> 27:57.050
Just...this folded-up bird made of paper.

27:59.469 --> 28:02.097
- Like origami?
- Yeah, like that.

28:02.764 --> 28:04.141
<i>Like origami.</i>

28:38.550 --> 28:40.552
You're Charles Westmoreland, right?

28:40.636 --> 28:43.847
- Do I know you?
- Knew your wife before she passed.

28:44.306 --> 28:46.516
- You knew Marla?
- You mean Ann?

28:47.476 --> 28:50.687
- How'd you know her?
- We taught together in Boston.

28:50.812 --> 28:53.690
- East Farmington.
- You mean West Wilmington?

28:54.483 --> 28:57.194
No more tests, I promise.

28:58.820 --> 29:01.031
Seems you know everything about me.

29:01.114 --> 29:03.283
- Who are you?
- Michael Scofield.

29:03.742 --> 29:07.371
- How'd you get it in here?
- First off, she's not an it.

29:07.913 --> 29:10.415
She's Marilyn, and she's grandfathered

29:10.499 --> 29:12.751
back from the days
when prisoners were allowed

29:12.834 --> 29:15.212
a creature comfort or two.

29:15.295 --> 29:17.339
Heard you were D.B. Cooper.

29:18.674 --> 29:21.843
Every new fish comes in here,
first thing they hear

29:21.927 --> 29:24.513
is that Charles Westmoreland's
D.B. Cooper.

29:24.888 --> 29:27.057
I'll tell you like I tell them.

29:28.100 --> 29:29.977
You want the Cooper story?

29:30.060 --> 29:32.854
I can't give it to you 'cause I'm not him.

29:33.146 --> 29:35.941
That's too bad. Sort of wish it was true.

29:36.149 --> 29:37.567
Man's a legend.

29:37.651 --> 29:40.529
Nowhere near as much
as I wish it were true, friend.

29:40.612 --> 29:43.365
I'd have $1.5 million waiting for me
on the outside.

29:46.535 --> 29:49.079
I'd put some grass under them
if I were you.

29:50.247 --> 29:53.625
This thing would go a whole lot easier
if you'd just hire me.

29:53.709 --> 29:55.502
What is this all about?

29:56.378 --> 29:59.214
Say you were able
to get outside those walls.

29:59.298 --> 30:02.384
Would you have the people in place
to make sure you disappeared forever?

30:02.467 --> 30:05.220
- What do you care?
- Just curious.

30:05.345 --> 30:08.515
- Where's Fibonacci?
- That's not the way it works.

30:13.562 --> 30:16.481
They come at me, John,
I'm coming after you.

30:17.357 --> 30:18.525
I doubt it.

30:44.843 --> 30:45.886
(ALARM BUZZING)

30:45.969 --> 30:47.471
All right.

30:51.767 --> 30:53.477
On the ground! On the ground!

30:53.560 --> 30:55.103
Get on the ground!

30:56.772 --> 31:01.401
I totally misjudged you, Scofield.
I didn't think you were the agitating type.

31:01.485 --> 31:04.196
Behavior like that
will not be tolerated in my prison.

31:04.279 --> 31:05.572
Ninety days in the SHU.

31:05.655 --> 31:07.908
That ought to be enough time
to convince you of that fact.

31:07.991 --> 31:09.618
- Ninety days?
- That's right.

31:17.709 --> 31:19.711
Something you want to say?

31:20.045 --> 31:21.463
It's just...

31:22.130 --> 31:24.257
I'm not of much value to you in the SHU.

31:24.341 --> 31:26.802
- Value?
- The Taj.

31:27.427 --> 31:29.805
It'd be a shame for the eighth wonder
of the modern world

31:29.888 --> 31:32.682
to collapse because the stress
isn't properly propagated.

31:32.766 --> 31:35.477
- Properly propagated?
- Properly propagated.

31:35.560 --> 31:37.437
The joints are overloaded.

31:37.521 --> 31:39.773
They won't provide anywhere near
the sheer strength

31:39.856 --> 31:42.150
the completed structure will need.

31:42.818 --> 31:44.945
How much work are we talking?

31:45.028 --> 31:47.322
- You want it by when, June?
- Yes.

31:47.656 --> 31:50.492
Then we better get started,
wouldn't you say?

32:15.600 --> 32:17.185
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

32:17.269 --> 32:18.728
Who's there?

32:36.830 --> 32:41.334
Bishop McMorrow was killed last night.
Someone shot him while he was sleeping.

32:41.835 --> 32:45.005
- I thought you'd want to know.
- Thanks.

32:52.429 --> 32:54.055
Michael was right.

33:23.502 --> 33:25.462
Sink, you got a visitor.

33:38.016 --> 33:39.559
He was arrested.

33:41.228 --> 33:43.730
- For what?
- Possession of marijuana.

33:47.108 --> 33:50.028
I figured he could use
some fatherly advice before it's...

33:51.655 --> 33:53.657
- Gone forever?
- I didn't mean that.

33:53.740 --> 33:56.243
I know you didn't. Thanks, Lisa.

33:57.953 --> 33:59.037
Sit down.

34:04.292 --> 34:05.544
DOpe, huh?

34:05.961 --> 34:07.295
Using or dealing?

34:08.755 --> 34:10.297
What's the difference?

34:10.382 --> 34:13.760
Then what? You think it gives you
some kind of street cred?

34:15.469 --> 34:18.223
You got a piece of the good life.
Take advantage.

34:19.139 --> 34:21.643
Look, I get it, the whole thing.

34:22.310 --> 34:24.145
She drags me in here,

34:24.563 --> 34:27.649
you give me a big speech,
I walk away a changed man.

34:27.899 --> 34:31.570
Straight A's, Harvard,
grow up and be a dentist.

34:32.279 --> 34:33.989
It's better than being here.

34:35.364 --> 34:39.159
You got to realize who's getting punished
when you're doing the things you're doing.

34:39.244 --> 34:42.246
You think it's me. It's you.
I did the same thing.

34:42.330 --> 34:46.126
Punished the old man 'cause he was gone.
Look what it got me.

34:49.254 --> 34:51.797
I'm not asking you to love me.

34:51.880 --> 34:54.717
I already screwed up that chance long ago.

34:54.801 --> 34:56.928
I'm asking you to love yourself.

34:57.012 --> 34:59.347
You can still put the brakes on this thing.

35:01.224 --> 35:03.685
So, that's what fatherly advice is like.

35:04.603 --> 35:06.354
Where are you going?

35:06.855 --> 35:08.356
I got homework.

35:09.190 --> 35:11.401
They're putting me to death, LJ.

35:11.484 --> 35:13.403
In a month's time, I'll be dead.

35:14.112 --> 35:15.322
You get that?

35:17.115 --> 35:18.617
You're already dead to me.

35:26.374 --> 35:28.668
(LATIN MUSIC PLAYING ON STEREO)

35:29.878 --> 35:31.212
(SPEAKING IN SPANISH)

35:44.142 --> 35:45.226
Yes.

35:45.852 --> 35:48.563
What? You mean, "yes" yes?

35:49.064 --> 35:50.440
Yes, yes!

35:53.902 --> 35:55.570
- There's just one thing.
- Of course.

35:55.654 --> 35:58.448
- Mama wants us to wait till you get out.
- Of course, <i>mi amor.</i>

35:58.531 --> 36:00.950
- Only we have to get married in a church.
- Okay, <i>est√© bien.</i>

36:01.034 --> 36:02.202
A Catholic church.

36:02.285 --> 36:05.330
Wouldn't want to mess
with the Catholic roots, would we?

36:11.086 --> 36:13.755
- You went to Loyola.
- You've been checking up on me.

36:13.838 --> 36:15.632
I like to get to know my patients.

36:15.715 --> 36:18.093
I went to Northwestern.
Graduated two years after you did.

36:18.176 --> 36:21.554
Maybe we met before.
You know, drunk, out at a bar somewhere.

36:21.638 --> 36:22.972
I would've remembered.

36:23.056 --> 36:24.849
- That a compliment?
- No.

36:28.186 --> 36:29.270
What?

36:29.354 --> 36:32.065
Your blood glucose
is at 50 milligrams per deciliter.

36:32.148 --> 36:34.025
I _ ~30?
- ts hypoglycemic,

36:34.275 --> 36:37.153
Your body's reacting to the insulin
like you're not a diabetic.

36:37.237 --> 36:41.116
- You sure it's Type I diabetes you got?
- Ever since I was a kid.

36:41.700 --> 36:44.661
All right. Not experiencing
any tingling sensation, cold sweats?

36:44.744 --> 36:46.287
(PHONE RINGING)

36:49.040 --> 36:50.125
Infirmary.

36:50.542 --> 36:51.626
Yes.

36:53.002 --> 36:54.671
Yeah, I did.

36:55.922 --> 36:57.966
No, I did and I do. I need to go.

36:59.259 --> 37:00.343
Okay.

37:01.302 --> 37:05.765
Great. Well, I'll call him after lunch then.
Thanks. I'm with a patient. Okay.

37:05.849 --> 37:08.268
I'd like to run some tests
next time you're in.

37:08.351 --> 37:11.938
Last thing I want is to be administering
insulin to a man who doesn't need it.

37:12.021 --> 37:13.440
Yeah, sure.

37:14.107 --> 37:15.191
Okay.

37:22.157 --> 37:25.493
- How'd you get here by the way?
- Oh, you know.

37:26.536 --> 37:28.496
I don't. That's why I asked.

37:28.997 --> 37:31.499
- You know. Hector.
- What?

37:32.125 --> 37:35.462
I didn't have any money for the bus,
so he offered me a ride.

37:35.545 --> 37:37.172
He was really sweet.

37:38.840 --> 37:41.593
- Honey, he's just a friend.
- No, he's not just a friend.

37:41.676 --> 37:44.888
I know Hector. I know men.
Men and women can't be friends.

37:44.971 --> 37:48.808
A guy doesn't drive a girl 500 miles across
state lines because he wants to be friends.

37:48.892 --> 37:49.851
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

37:49.934 --> 37:51.644
GUARD: Casanova, wrap it up.

37:52.187 --> 37:55.315
Hey, you got nothing
to worry about, okay?

37:55.857 --> 37:59.527
- It's you I'm marrying.
- It's not you I'm worried about.

38:02.238 --> 38:03.907
Sixteen more months.

38:12.624 --> 38:13.792
I love you.

38:25.386 --> 38:27.555
Be easy, son, all right?

38:33.394 --> 38:36.147
Sucre tells me you're the local pharmacy.

38:39.734 --> 38:41.736
- What you need, man?
- PUGNAc.

38:42.070 --> 38:44.197
I only speak English, white boy.

38:44.280 --> 38:45.406
It's an insulin blocker.

38:45.490 --> 38:48.201
Standard over-the-counter variety
you can get at any pharmacy.

38:48.284 --> 38:51.287
- You can get that at Medical then.
- I can't get that at Medical.

38:51.371 --> 38:52.580
Why not?

38:52.664 --> 38:55.750
Because they're already
giving me insulin shots.

38:56.876 --> 38:59.254
You're one mixed-up cracker,
you know that?

38:59.337 --> 39:01.005
Can you get it for me or not?

39:01.840 --> 39:05.301
Only if you tell me why is it you want
to keep going back up to Medical

39:05.385 --> 39:07.679
to get an insulin shot
which you don't need.

39:07.762 --> 39:09.389
I like the ambience.

39:10.598 --> 39:12.100
Are we in business?

39:27.240 --> 39:28.616
Scofield.

39:28.700 --> 39:29.951
I don't know what you did,

39:30.034 --> 39:32.829
but Abruzzi wanted me
to give you this Pl card.

39:32.912 --> 39:36.374
Congratulations.
You just joined the ranks of the employed.

39:52.473 --> 39:53.850
Kudos, Fish.

39:54.559 --> 39:56.144
You got spine.

40:02.108 --> 40:04.402
All right, cons, break it down!

40:06.529 --> 40:08.323
Move it, guys.

40:16.831 --> 40:18.249
(BELL RINGING)

40:20.126 --> 40:22.045
Saw Veronica came by yesterday.

40:22.128 --> 40:24.255
- Still engaged to that guy?
- Yep.

40:24.672 --> 40:27.717
- Could've been me.
- If you hadn't self-destructed.

40:29.010 --> 40:31.429
You think I meant to knock up Lisa Rix?

40:31.638 --> 40:33.723
I was just being stupid. Hurt.

40:35.850 --> 40:39.979
- Shouldn't have pushed her away, though.
- You pushed everyone away.

40:40.063 --> 40:43.399
I'm an anchor.
All I'll do is drag them down with me.

40:48.780 --> 40:50.281
Why did you hire him?

40:50.365 --> 40:53.868
Keep your friends close,
your enemies closer.

40:59.290 --> 41:03.127
- You mean what you said earlier?
- I'm not here on vacation, trust me.

41:04.545 --> 41:07.507
Getting outside these walls
is just the beginning.

41:07.590 --> 41:09.300
You're gonna need money.

41:12.261 --> 41:13.721
I'll have it.

41:14.180 --> 41:17.850
And people on the outside.
People that can help you disappear.

41:18.226 --> 41:19.769
I've already got them.

41:20.561 --> 41:22.438
They just don't know it yet.

41:27.068 --> 41:31.406
Look, whatever you got going on,
fill me in 'cause I'm in the dark here.

41:32.573 --> 41:36.285
Chaparral Associates got the contract
to retrofit this place in '99.

41:36.369 --> 41:37.704
$4 million contract.

41:37.787 --> 41:41.124
Head partner couldn't crack it,
so he subcontracted out.

41:41.207 --> 41:43.459
An under-the-table sort of deal
with a former associate.

41:43.543 --> 41:46.421
That guy was one of the partners
in my firm.

41:48.673 --> 41:50.466
We basically ghostwrote the whole plan.

41:50.550 --> 41:53.636
Crossed the t's, dotted the I's,
grouted the tiles.

42:02.770 --> 42:05.106
- You've seen the blueprints.
- Better than that.

42:06.691 --> 42:08.234
I've got them on me.

42:12.280 --> 42:13.614
Are you kidding me?

42:17.201 --> 42:19.287
